  "texts": [
    "Although these web pages appear straightforward and present the relevant information about the objects in a human-readable fashion (see Figure 3), underlying Hyper-Text Markup Language (HTML) reveals significant differences in structure among websites.",
    "Some adopt structured graph databases, making data retrieval easy for both users and software thanks to their contextual schemas.",
    "Conversely, many websites rely on HTML elements (such as headings, paragraphs, lists, etc.)",
    "combined with Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) selectors for content organisation.",
    "CSS selectors enable selective styling of HTML elements or groups of elements, enhancing the visual appeal and layout."
  ],
